                android:text="Prepare the Sauce:

In a bowl, mix together tamarind paste, fish sauce, soy sauce, brown sugar, and chili paste. Adjust the ingredients to achieve a balance of sweet, salty, and tangy flavors.
Prepare the Noodles:

Soak the rice noodles in warm water until they become pliable, following the package instructions. Drain and set aside.
Cook the Pad Thai:

Heat vegetable oil in a wok or large pan over medium-high heat.

Add cubed tofu and cook until golden brown. If using shrimp or chicken, cook until they are cooked through.

Push the tofu, shrimp, or chicken to the side of the wok. Add minced garlic to the center and cook until fragrant.

Add the beaten eggs to the center and scramble until cooked.

Add the soaked and drained rice noodles to the wok.

Pour the prepared sauce over the noodles. Use tongs to toss everything together until the noodles are evenly coated with the sauce.

Add bean sprouts and sliced green onions. Toss again to combine.

Taste and adjust the seasoning if needed.

Serve:

Transfer the Pad Thai to serving plates.

Garnish with crushed peanuts, fresh cilantro, and lime wedges.

Optionally, add extra bean sprouts on the side.

Serve immediately and enjoy your homemade Pad Thai!"
